poéticos. Se trata de mostrar cómo algunos de estos han servido para la
construcción de un pensamiento artístico y académico; para la construcción de
obras concretas tanto en la Ciudad Abierta como en las Travesías; y para la
formación de arquitectos y diseñadores junto a otras disciplinas tanto artísticas,
científicas, humanistas y técnicas, durante más de sesenta años. Para ello,
primeramente, se revisa aquí el estado del arte de la metáfora.
Existe un cuerpo documental en el Archivo Histórico José Vial Armstrong que
consiste en cassettes grabados con muchas de las clases de Godofredo Iommi,
entre 1978 y 1997. Esta tesis abarca y se limita a las metáforas contenidas en estas
grabaciones.
Es importante comprender a cabalidad cómo fueron construidos estos
enunciados metafóricos, cuáles fueron sus efectos concretos y qué oportunidad
existe hoy para que este quehacer metafórico pueda continuar desarrollando la
relación entre la poesía y los oficios en la Escuela, pero además enriquezca el
ámbito global de toda la universidad y de muchas disciplinas. En este sentido la
hipótesis considera que los enunciados metafóricos pueden ser esenciales para la
construcción del conocimiento y además la construcción material del mundo.
Mediante una relación a través del trabajo y el estudio entre diferentes oficios,
estos enunciados metafóricos no sólo se transforman en puentes y conductos
comunicantes mediante los cuales las disciplinas se alimentan unas de otras, sino
que son en sí mismos creadores de realidades disciplinares. Ciencia, arte y
humanidades convergen en la creación de novedad transformadas por los
enunciados metafóricos de la palabra poética."	"Metáfora;poesía;ciencia;universidad;Iommi"	"Godofredo Iommi (1917-2001), argentine poet, with a group of architects and
artists, refounded the School of Architecture and Design of the Pontifical Catholic
University of Valparaíso, Chile, in 1952, based on the idea that there is a
relationship between poetry and trades. This relationship has been implemented
since the early days and is responsible for the artistic, intellectual and academic
production of the members of this School.One of the direct consequences of the
relationship between poetry and trades was the founding of the Open City in the
early 1970s; A place where it has tried to reunite the life, the work and the study,
by a community that is governed under poetic and artistic precepts.The hypothesis
of this thesis is that Godofredo Iommi, as a poet, contributed decisively to the
development of this School and the Open City, through the construction of
metaphors, metaphorical processes or poetic metaphorical statements. It is about
showing how some of these have served to construct an artistic and academic
thinking; for the construction of concrete works both in the Open City and in the
Travesías; and for the training of architects and designers along with other artistic,
scientific, humanistic and technical disciplines, for more than sixty years. For this,
the state of the art of metaphor is reviewed here.There is a documentary corpus in
the José Vial Armstrong Historical Archive which consists of cassettes recorded
with many of classes by Godofredo Iommi between 1978 and 1997. This thesis
covers and is limited to the metaphors contained in these recordings.It is
important to fully understand how these metaphorical statements were
constructed, what their concrete effects were and what opportunity exists today so
that this metaphorical work can continue to develop the relationship between
poetry and trades in the School, but also enriches the global scope of all the
university and many disciplines. In this sense the hypothesis considers that the
metaphorical statements can be essential for the material construction of the world
and knowledge. Through a relationship between work and study in different
trades, these metaphorical statements not only become bridges and
communicating channels through which disciplines feed on each other, but are
themselves creators of disciplinary realities. Science, art and the humanities
converge in the creation of new realities transformed by the metaphorical
statements of the poetic word."	"Metaphor;poetry;science;university;Iommi."	"1"	"204"	"ESPANHOL"	"PUC-Rio"	"Design e Sociedade"	"DESIGN: COMUNICAÇÃO, CULTURA E ARTES"		"NILTON GONCALVES GAMBA JUNIOR"	"Sim"	"Rodrigo Saavedra Venegas"	"Participante Externo"	""	""	""	""	""	""				"Sim"
"O hibridismo e a expansão das narrativas no livro-objeto infantil contemporâneo"	"DISSERTAÇÃO"	"ANA PAULA FONSECA DE OLIVEIRA"	"OLIVEIRA, A. P. F."	"11/04/2017"	"Esta dissertação discute o hibridismo presente nos livros-objeto infantis contemporâneos,
na tentativa de evidenciar como os fundamentos da natureza híbrida da linguagem
do Design e a experiência intersemiótica revelam-se como interações presentes
em enredos multissensoriais, expandindo as narrativas encontradas no livro-objeto
infantil. O olhar sobre o ato de ler não se restringe à decifração de letras grafadas em
qualquer que seja o suporte, mas se expande para a absorção das representatividades
estabelecidas. O design de livros influencia a leitura não apenas em aspectos funcionais,
mas também simbólicos e, por isso, pode ser considerado um mediador de leitura, que
conduz o leitor em sua jornada. A dissertação apresenta a leitura de dois livros-objeto
infantis selecionados nas obras de Kv?ta Pacovská e Roger Mello, designers/ilustradores/
artistas plásticos reconhecidos internacionalmente com o prêmio Hans Christian
Andersen. Buscou-se verificar os processos com os quais são ativadas e ampliadas as suas
histórias no hibridismo dos processos narrativos. Para isso, a dissertação se apoiou na
concepção do híbrido como categoria analítica proposta por Braida (2012)."	"Livro-objeto;Design na leitura;hibridismo;mediação;livro infantil"	"This thesis discusses the hybridism in the contemporary children´s Object
Books, in an attempt to elucidate how the hybrid nature of the design language and
of the intersemiotic experience, reveal the interactions in the multisensory stories, expanding
the narratives found in children´s Object Books. A look at the act of reading
is not restricted to the deciphering of written letters ? in whatever sort of support,
but in the absorption of established representativeness. Book design influences that
?reading?, not only in functional aspects, but also in symbolic ones, and that is why it
can be considered as a reading-mediator, driving the reader through his journey. The
thesis presents the reading of two children´s object-books chosen from the works from
Kv?ta Pacovská and Roger Mello, both internationally recognized designers/illustrators
and plastic artists awarded with the Hans Christian Andersen prize. In these books,
the progress from which the histories were activated and amplified in the hybridism of
the narrative process was accounted. The theses is based on the notion of hybrid as an
analytical category as proposed by Braida (2012)."	"Object Book;reading design;hybridism;mediation;Children´s book"	"1"	"128"	"PORTUGUES"	"PUC-Rio"	"Design e Sociedade"	"DESIGN: COMUNICAÇÃO, CULTURA E ARTES"	"As tipologias da linguagem híbrida do design entre a teoria e a prática"	"VERA LUCIA MOREIRA DOS SANTOS NOJIMA"	"Sim"	""	""	"33654831000136"	"CONS NAC DE DESENVOLVIMENTO CIENTIFICO E TECNOLOGICO - CNPq/CAPES"	"24"	""	""	""				"Sim"
